{"cursor":"7708","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Ethnic group |group= Afro-Ecuadorian |poptime=c. 1,120,000 |popplace='[[South\nAmerica]]:' Ecuador  Esmeraldas, Valle del Chota, Imbabura Province,\nQuito and Guayaquil |langs=Spanish |rels=Predominantly Roman Catholic |related=Sub-\nsaharan Africans and other African groups. }}\n\n'Afro-Ecuadorians' are an ethnic group in Ecuador who are descendants of black\nAfrican slaves brought by the Spanish during their conquest of Ecuador from the\nIncas. They make up from 4% to 6% of Ecuador's population. [https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-\nfactbook/geos/ec.html CIA: The World Factbook] [http://www.pbs.org/fr-\nontlineworld/rough/2010/06/ecuador_dreamto.html Frontline/World, Ecuador:\nDreamtown]\n\nEcuador has a population of about 1,120,000 descendants from African people. The\nAfro-Ecuadorian culture is found primarily in the country's northwest coastal\nregion. Africans form a majority (70%) in the province of Esmeraldas and the\nValle del Chota in the Imbabura Province. They can be also found in Quito and\nGuayaquil. Their best known cultural influence known outside of Ecuador is a\ndistinctive kind of marimba music.\n","linknr":296,"url":"Afroecuatoriano","recorded":1374547205,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Afro_Ecuadorian&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Afro_Ecuadorian&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","/wiki/Afro_Ecuadorian","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=sty